# Sierra Linux QMI drivers builder

- Process of building and installing kernel modules using Dynamic Kernel Module Support (DKMS)

# Licensing

- This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify it under
the terms of the GNU General Public License version 2 and only version 2 as
published by the Free Software Foundation.

# Requirements

- Recent modern [Bash](https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/)
- Recent version of [DKMS](https://github.com/dell/dkms)
- All the other requirements as listed on the [driver package page](https://source.sierrawireless.com/resources/airprime/software/usb-drivers-linux-qmi-software-latest/) on the Sierra Wireless website.

# Build Instructions

- Extract driver tarball to `/usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62`:
```
sudo mkdir -p /usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62
sudo tar -C /usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62 -xvf SierraLinuxQMIdriversS2.42N2.62.tar.bz2
```

- Copy dkms.conf to `/usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62`:
```
sudo cp /usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62/dkms/dkms.conf /usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62/
```

- Add the modules to the DKMS tree:
```
sudo dkms add --verbose -m SierraLinuxQMIdrivers -v S2.42N2.62
```

- Build the modules using DKMS:
```
sudo dkms build --verbose -m SierraLinuxQMIdrivers -v S2.42N2.62
```

- Install the modules using DKMS:
```
sudo dkms install --verbose -m SierraLinuxQMIdrivers -v S2.42N2.62
```

- Check status:
```
sudo dkms status --verbose -m SierraLinuxQMIdrivers -v S2.42N2.62
```

- Uninstall and remove source using DKMS:
```
sudo dkms uninstall --verbose -m SierraLinuxQMIdrivers -v S2.42N2.62
sudo dkms remove --verbose -m SierraLinuxQMIdrivers -v S2.42N2.62 --all
sudo rm -fR /usr/src/SierraLinuxQMIdrivers-S2.42N2.62
```

## Notes

- **IMPORTANT** The Sierra build installs the modules into /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/kernel/drivers/net/usb /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/kernel/drivers/usb/serial/, but dkms ignores the corresponding DEST_MODULE_LOCATION in the dkms.conf for Ubuntu, as per design, putting the modules into /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/updates/dkms instead
